#Directory creation
A directory is just a folder. It helps organize files. 
Example: "Downloads" or "Documents" are directories.

#Mkdir – Make Directory
Definition:mkdir stands for "make directory". It creates a new folder (directory).
Example: mkdir MyFolder,mkdir Aish
This creates a folder called MyFolder in your current location.

#touch – Make File
Definition:touch is used to create a new empty file. It’s often used to make text or code files.
Example: touch myfile.txt,touch Aish.txt (type ls to see the file).
